<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="140" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1015,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">
The features of southern Central Asian 
<taxonomicName authority="Prout, 1912" box="[580,742,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hierochthonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[580,742,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Hierochthonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<taxonomicName authority="Warren, 1901" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1901" box="[843,1138,1015,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hierochthonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulverata">
<emphasis box="[843,863,1016,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[875,982,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">pulverata</emphasis>
Warren, 1901
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1239,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[253,1325,784,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-271@5.[248,1339,777,1872]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Genitalia structures of Hierochthonia, Ratsa, gen. nov. and Xenochlorodes. 22: Hierochthonia pulverata: 22a—male armature, 22b—aedeagus, 22c—VIII sternite, 22d—lateral view; 23–24: Ratsa alexandraria: 23a—male armature, 23b—aedeagus, 23c—VIII sternite, 23d—lateral view, 24a—female genitalia, lateral view, 24b—female genitalia, ventral view; 25—female genitalia of Ratsa? petitaria; 26—female genitalia of Xenochlorodes albicostaria. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566160/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pungeler, 1902))" authorityName="Pungeler. Comparison" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hierochthonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semitaria">
<emphasis box="[1298,1318,1016,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1330,1436,1016,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">semitaria</emphasis>
(Püngeler, 1902))
</taxonomicName>
stressed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hausmann, A." box="[493,696,1051,1078]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" pagination="3 - 90" refId="ref4374" refString="Hausmann, A. (1996) The morphology of the geometrid moths of the Levant and neighbouring countries. Part I: Orthostixinae, Geometrinae. Nota lepidopterologica, 19 (1 / 2), 3 - 90." type="journal article" year="1996">Hausmann (1996)</bibRefCitation>
are missing in Middle Asian species “ 
<emphasis box="[1139,1337,1051,1078]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">
H.” 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1912" box="[1191,1337,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Ratsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandraria">alexandraria</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, e.g. the long postvaginal sclerite in the female genitalia, or the spoon-shaped aedeagus with a complex apical ornamentation in the male (compare 
<figureCitation box="[395,565,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[253,1325,784,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-271@5.[248,1339,777,1872]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Genitalia structures of Hierochthonia, Ratsa, gen. nov. and Xenochlorodes. 22: Hierochthonia pulverata: 22a—male armature, 22b—aedeagus, 22c—VIII sternite, 22d—lateral view; 23–24: Ratsa alexandraria: 23a—male armature, 23b—aedeagus, 23c—VIII sternite, 23d—lateral view, 24a—female genitalia, lateral view, 24b—female genitalia, ventral view; 25—female genitalia of Ratsa? petitaria; 26—female genitalia of Xenochlorodes albicostaria. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566160/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Figs 22 and 23</figureCitation>
). The characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prout" authorityYear="1912" box="[832,1147,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hierochthonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alexandraria">
<emphasis box="[832,1147,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Hierochthonia alexandraria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reviewed below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1015,1294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">
The plate-shaped medial harpe (
<figureCitation box="[557,638,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[447,1139,982,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-332@2.[447,1139,982,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Genitalia structures of Hissarica and Hierochthonia. 14–15: Hissarica postalbida. 14a—male armature with aedeagus, 14b—VIII sternite of male; 15—female genitalia (15a–part of bursa with signum enlarged); 16: Xenochlorodes olympiaria: 16a—male armature, 16b—aedeagus, 16c—VIII sternite of male. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566154/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) and the signum with a long filiform ridge in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viidalepp" authorityYear="1988" box="[1147,1256,1160,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hissarica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1256,1160,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Hissarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1270,1351,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1865,1889]" captionTargetBox="[447,1139,982,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-332@2.[447,1139,982,1842]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Genitalia structures of Hissarica and Hierochthonia. 14–15: Hissarica postalbida. 14a—male armature with aedeagus, 14b—VIII sternite of male; 15—female genitalia (15a–part of bursa with signum enlarged); 16: Xenochlorodes olympiaria: 16a—male armature, 16b—aedeagus, 16c—VIII sternite of male. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566154/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) do not have morphological equivalents in southern species. Again, the long lamella postvaginalis and roundish dilations lateral to it figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hausmann, A." box="[400,595,1231,1258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" pagination="3 - 90" refId="ref4374" refString="Hausmann, A. (1996) The morphology of the geometrid moths of the Levant and neighbouring countries. Part I: Orthostixinae, Geometrinae. Nota lepidopterologica, 19 (1 / 2), 3 - 90." type="journal article" year="1996">Hausmann (1996</bibRefCitation>
, Figs 144, 145) for southern 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1131,1231,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Hierochthonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[916,1078,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Hierochthonia</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
are absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[1285,1366,1231,1257]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" genus="Middle" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="3" pageNumber="144" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Middle</taxonomicName>
Asian species (
<figureCitation box="[247,378,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1897,1921]" captionTargetBox="[253,1325,784,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-271@5.[248,1339,777,1872]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Genitalia structures of Hierochthonia, Ratsa, gen. nov. and Xenochlorodes. 22: Hierochthonia pulverata: 22a—male armature, 22b—aedeagus, 22c—VIII sternite, 22d—lateral view; 23–24: Ratsa alexandraria: 23a—male armature, 23b—aedeagus, 23c—VIII sternite, 23d—lateral view, 24a—female genitalia, lateral view, 24b—female genitalia, ventral view; 25—female genitalia of Ratsa? petitaria; 26—female genitalia of Xenochlorodes albicostaria. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5566160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5566160/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="140">Figs 24, 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
